tweet:
@EpsilonTheory @bradmillscan @J9Roem @patestevao @glozow Your KYC data is *already* sent to Treasury if over $10k from a regulated exchange. Under this reg, the *recipient* data would be as well. https://t.co/t0Odmm3JIt

I'm no fan of the reg, but you can still mine, earn #BTC, hold your own coins, take part in a closed-loop economy...

name: elizabeth stark 🍠
tweet:
@EpsilonTheory @bradmillscan @J9Roem @patestevao @glozow Alas the proposed reg doesn't say what you think it does. It says regulated exchanges have to collect recipient data over thresholds. There is zero concept of a "federally-registered account". You can still send to your own wallet.

Always happy to chat with friendly skeptics. ;)
